Reasoning: The paper introduces a new objective function for learning in deep generative models, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The focus on learning in deep generative models suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The use of variational inference and autoencoders suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely sub-category. The evaluation of the TVO on continuous and discrete models suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also relevant sub-categories. Finally, the use of the TVO for inference compilation suggests that cs.SY (Systems and Control) may also be a relevant sub-category.
